comment:
* An {@link ExerciseCompletionGoal} that requires covering a specified distance. Additionally, * the step is not complete until the specified time has elapsed. Time remaining after the * specified distance has been completed should be spent resting. In the context of swimming, * this is sometimes referred to as 'interval training'. * *

For example, a swimming coach may specify '100m @ 1min40s'. This implies: complete 100m * and if you manage it in 1min30s, you will have 10s of rest prior to the next set.

methods.name: public Length getDistance()
methods.comment: Returns the total distance that must be covered to complete this goal.

methods.name: public Duration getDuration()
methods.comment: Returns the total duration that must elapse to complete this goal.
